<div id="gameContainer" style="height: 600px; margin: auto" position: relative></div>
<div style="position: absolute; top: 38%; left: 53%; transform: translate(-50%, -50%); margin: 0; padding: 0; width: 100%">
    <div class="container">
        <div class="row d-flex align-items-lg-center flex-wrap g-mb-60 g-mb-0--lg">
            <div class="col-md-2 col-lg-2"></div>
            <div class="col-md-8 col-lg-8">
                <h2 class="g-color-white g-font-size-36 text-uppercase g-line-height-1_2 g-mb-30">
                    <span class="g-font-weight-900 g-color-primary">
                        PROJ: <span class="g-font-weight-600">Ray Marcher</span>
                        <div class="g-color-white g-font-weight-400" style="display: inline-block">/ Sphere Tracer</div>
                    </span>
                </h2>

                <p class="g-color-gray-light-v5 g-font-size-16 g-mb-35 pull-right">
                    A <span class="g-color-primary g-font-weight-600">signed distance functions (SDF)</span> is a method of returning 
                    the shortest distance between a coordinate and a surface. We render these SDFs in the scene using a
                    <span class="g-color-primary g-font-weight-600">ray marching</span>
                    algorithm, also commonly referred to as sphere tracing.
                    <br /><br />SDF's can also be used for generating interesting 3D fractals. My goal is to use this ray marching
                    framework I have built to generate future dynamic and detailed fractals.
                </p>

                <a href="#" class="btn btn-xl btn-primary g-font-weight-600 g-letter-spacing-0_5 text-uppercase text-left rounded-0 g-mr-10 g-mb-15">
                    <span class="pull-left">
                        Play Demo Online
